The cocycle function 

Calculating the cocycle function is heavily dependent on knowing appropriate 
heat kernel coefficients. These heat kernel coefficients are defined in  
dimensions by an asymptotic expansion,
 
In five dimensions we require , which can be found in the 
literature. It takes the form of a surface integral of scalar 
invariants with a maximum of four derivatives of the metric.

