Zero modes 
Here we discuss a slight subtlety with boundary conditions. Note, by zero modes 
we mean the  modes in our mode sum and not null eigenvectors.
In we considered the case of a scalar field, but 
neglected the zero modes because from the one brane 
point of view it is more convenient to consider , which has no 
boundaries. 
